    <ul class="news-list">
     <li class="news-item">
      <h4 id="5b100232-56ad-4a11-a292-6b5b7915883d">
       Undergraduate math major honored by Association for Women in Mathematics
       <a href="#5b100232-56ad-4a11-a292-6b5b7915883d">
        <small>
         (Jan 18, 2019)
        </small>
       </a>
      </h4>
      <p>
       Naomi Sweeting, a fourth-year in the College, has been awarded the Alice T. Schafer Mathematics Prize, given annually by the Association for Women in Mathematics (AWM) to an undergraduate woman for excellence in mathematics.
      </p>
      <p>
       <a href="https://physical-sciences.uchicago.edu/news/undergraduate-honored-association-women-mathematics">
        Read more here
       </a>
       .
      </p>
     </li>
